<TEXT>
jim and tammy bakker begin broadcasting a 
new television show from their living room monday for at least six 
independent television stations across the nation according to a 
published report 
bakker and three of his associates were indicted this month on 
charges of misusing millions of dollars in ptl funds bakker could 
not be reached for comment thursday 
the charlotte observer in fridays editions quoted unidentified 
sources as saying that the live broadcasts from the bakkers living 
room near pineville will be carried on stations in albany ny 
atlanta chico calif los angeles philadelphia and san diego 
bakker attorney jim toms of hendersonville nc said in a 
telephone interview thursday night that the bakkers had been 
preparing to return to television but could not confirm when the 
return would take place 
bakker has not had a regular tv show since he resigned from ptl 
in march 1987 after widely publicized allegations of his 1980 sexual 
encounter with church secretary jessica hahn and payments to keep 
her quiet 
</TEXT>
