<TEXT>
john e mcknight former managing editor of 
the sumter item died tuesday he was 76 
mcknight began his newspaper career at the age of 6 when he sold 
the the charleston evening post at a railroad station in his 
native williamsburg county he was a sports editor and wire editor 
at the florence morning news before moving to sumter in 1936 as news 
editor 
mcknight retired in 1967 from the item he also was a past 
president of the south carolina associated press news council 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
julius l jack meier jr retired 
chairman of the meier amp frank co department stores died tuesday of 
congestive heart failure he was 76 
meier was the son julius l meier president of meier amp frank 
and grandson of aaron meier who in 1857 founded the mercantile 
outlet that grew into oregons largest department store chain 
in 1965 meier guided the negotiations that led to meier amp frank 
becoming part of the may department stores chain he continued as 
president and general manager of the portlandbased meier amp frank 
stores until 1969 when he was elevated to board chairman he 
retired in 1972 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
charlotte peters the star of a popular local 
television show that spanned more than 20 years died wednesday she 
was in he 70s 
mrs peters was a st louis housewife when she won a talent 
contest in 1947 singing id be lost without you and received a 
weeklong guest spot on the to the ladies show hosted by russ 
severin on st louis nbc affiliate ksd now ksdk 
because mrs peters was so poplular in the weeklong stint the 
station kept her on as a regular several years later the show 
became the charlotte peters show the show later moved to the 
abc affiliate ktvi and aired until 1969 
</TEXT>
