<TEXT>
dr carl j johnson an early and 
outspoken critic of the rocky flats nuclear weapons plant has died 
of complications from heart surgery he was 59 
johnson died thursday at the lutheran medical center in this 
denver suburb his son frederick said 
johnson was forced to resign as jefferson county health director 
in may 1981 following his publication of studies showing a higher 
incidence of cancer in areas of jefferson and denver counties close 
to the rocky flats plant 16 miles northwest of denver 
johnson sued numerous county officials over the firing he 
received a 150000 settlement in january 1985 
they fired the messenger for the message said john holland 
the attorney who represented johnson in the case they killed off 
the communitys public health director for proving that the 
community had a major illness 
to me carl johnson was truly a great man his death is a 
tragedy in that its too early 
holland said johnson accomplished a great portion of his 
mission which was to revitalize the peoples right to live in a safe 
setting 
johnsons supporters said the government is now starting to 
acknowledge points he had been making for years 
for example the department of energy recently compiled a 
modernization report which calls for improvements to the nations 
nuclear weapons facilities through the year 2010 
according to a summary of the 250 billion energy department 
plan rocky flats recycling buildings would be upgraded between 
1990 and 1997 to continue operating safely as the plant is gradually 
shut down and relocated 
johnson recently had been doing consulting work on the effects of 
nuclear radiation holland said he wrote and published articles 
including a dec 18 column in the new york times headlined rocky 
flats death inc 
if the nation is to be properly protected all studies of 
nuclear contamination and associated health effects should be 
conducted primarily by independent scientists who are insulated from 
cynical retaliation he wrote 
the sims ind native received his medical degree in 1965 from 
ohio state university college of medicine he also held a masters 
degree in public health from the university of california school of 
public health at berkeley 
he became jefferson county health director in 1973 
following his resignation he spent five years as a medical 
officer with the south dakota health department in pierre sd he 
recently returned to denver 
as controversy surrounding rocky flats built over the past four 
months johnson appeared and spoke at almost every public forum 
he also served as a colonel in the medical corps of the us army 
reserve from 1970 until his death 
johnson is survived by his wife kathryn and three sons 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

