failed the old exam charged it put too much emphasis on upperbody 
strength and did not reflect the physical demands of police work 
the new test implemented as part of an outofcourt settlement 
stresses flexibility and endurance 
men and women also must meet different standards and are measured 
against national averages for people of the same age and gender 
the new tests were administered between august and october to 13 
women and 113 men vying for 25 openings at the police academy 
