have elected you madam prime minister to lead your great country 
forward to peace and prosperity rooted in democracy we rejoice 
in the prospect of friendship and cooperation between india and 
pakistan gandhi said 
after the 2hour opening session gandhi and his wife sonia 
met privately over dinner with ms bhutto and her husband 
businessman asif zardari 
gandhi and ms bhuttos session this afternoon was to last up to 
two hours much longer than those she scheduled with other visiting 
leaders gandhi and ms bhutto are to meet again saturday after the 
summit ends 
although ms bhutto did not refer to gandhi in her inaugural 
speech she said last week that continued animosity between india 
and pakistan did not serve the interest of their peoples 
the two countries have fought three wars since they were 
partitioned in 1947 upon the demise of british colonial india 
relations have further been strained by a border dispute over 
kashmir which was split between pakistan and india when the 
subcontinent was divided india claims part of the territory in 
pakistan 
protesters have demonstrated daily in islamabad against indias 
claim sardar qayyum khan president of the pakistancontrolled part 
of kashmir said the protests have mobilized kashmiris on this 
side of the ceasefire line and have shown our integrity and 
solidarity with those suffering on the other side 
other areas of friction between the nations include fears of each 
others nuclear capabilities and claims that pakistan has supported 
sikh separatists who have killed 2400 people this year in indias 
border state of punjab pakistan has denied the charges 
so far pakistani and indian officials have declined to comment 
on the prospects of ms bhutto visiting india soon she has said her 
first foreign trips will be to china and saudi arabia she is 
expected to make a pilgrimage to mecca site of islams holiest 
shrine in january but no date has been set for a trip to beijing 
todays summit session was at damanekoh a whitedomed retreat 
on a hillside overlooking islamabad 
police with rifles stood at intervals of 20 feet to 150 feet 
other uniformed and plainclothes guards stood in clusters on rocky 
outcrops and among the trees and thickets 
the security was a reminder of the regions potential for 
violence 
both gandhi and sri lankan president junius r jayewardene have 
escaped unhurt from assassination attempts in their capitals while 
maldivian president maumoon abdul gayoom was the target of an 
unsuccessful coup less than two months ago 
another participant former gen hussain muhammad ershad of 
bangladesh assumed power in a bloodless coup in 1982 although a 
yesorno referendum subsequently proclaimed him president the 
other summit participants king birendra of nepal and king jigme 
singhe wangchuk of bhutan rule through hereditary succession 
