<TEXT>
a senior chinese official today marked the 10th 
anniversary of a chinese appeal for peaceful reunification with 
taiwan by renewing chinas proposal for direct talks with taiwans 
nationalist government 
we hold that the communist party and the kumomintang 
nationalists should establish contacts and start negotiations at 
an early date on the basis of equality vice premier wu xueqian 
said we can talk about the reunification of the country or carry 
out consultations on the concrete issues concerning the relations 
between the two sides 
wu was speaking at a forum of 300 senior party and government 
leaders held to commemorate chinas message to taiwan 
compatriots issued on jan 1 1979 
the message called for the peaceful reunification of taiwan with 
the mainland and proposed direct transportation and postal links as 
a first step toward easing tensions between the two nations 
the official xinhua news agency in a report on the forum said 
the 1979 message signified a historic turning point in relations 
between the mainland and taiwan 
china has since then called for direct political and trade 
contacts and has said taiwan can keep its current political and 
economic system if it rejoins the mainland 
the nationalists who fled to taiwan after their defeat to the 
communists in 1949 have rejected all proposals for direct contacts 
with the mainland however in the past year the taiwan government 
has eased travel and trade restrictions with the mainland 
more than 400000 taiwan residents have traveled to the mainland 
in the past year and indirect trade is estimated at 24 billion in 
1988 up from 15 billion in 1987 
such changes are in accordance with peoples wishes and the 
overall tendency of this historic development is therefore 
irreversible wu said 
he also expressed concern about taiwanese advocates of 
independence and those on the island who are in favor of two 
chinas or dual recognition concepts 
reunification is in the interests of both sides he said this 
will not only help the whole country to quickly become prosperous 
but will also help maintain sustained development on the island 
which can then enjoy the prestige of the great motherland 
