another indian source said theyre getting along famously 
pakistani officials declined comment on the talks 
before gandhi returns to new delhi on saturday india and 
pakistan are expected to sign three agreements including one in 
which the countries agree not to attack each others nuclear 
installations indian sources said 
the others provide for cultural exchanges and an end to double 
taxation in trade and commerce 
the signings appear to be largely symbolic and designed to 
emphasize hopes that new leadership in pakistan will lead to better 
relations with india 
