in 1973 president nixon received a subpoena to turn over white 
house tape recordings of conversations with top aides in connection 
with the watergate scandal although nixon was not required to 
testify the supreme court ruled that nixon had to release the tapes 
tate said she could not say whether bushs attorneys would fight 
the subpoena 
what theyre saying is that its unprecedented to do that 
she said in reference to potential bush testimony 
the issue of how much he knew about norths activities with the 
contras and the diversion of funds from iran was the subject of 
contradictory testimony during congressional hearings into the 
