<TEXT>
the inventors of the unbundled stock unit are 
confident they can tie up enough loose ends for stillunconvinced 
investors to make februarys planned offering of the new security a 
success 
but the developers who initially pitched the securities as a way 
to unlock hidden values in a company by breaking a share of its 
stock into three tradable components are now emphasizing the value 
of the three pieces as a package 
ron gallatin the shearson lehman hutton inc executive who 
oversaw the development of the unbundled stock unit insists the new 
marketing approach simply reflects an effort to point out what may 
have been an underappreciated reason for making the switch from 
common stock to unbundled stock unit 
there seems to be no question that long before the important 
date there will be more than enough people comfortable with it to 
proceed with the offerings he said 
the important date may be in early february after the securities 
and exchange commission completes its review of the proposal and the 
offerings begin 
shearson and four clients american express co pfizer inc 
dow chemical co and sara lee corp said dec 5 that they planned 
to offer shareholders a chance to exchange about 56 billion in 
common stock for unbundled stock units the precise exchange ratio 
has not been announced and some investors are pushing to get one 
unbundled unit for slightly less than a share of common 
the unbundled stock unit consists of a 30year bond paying 
interest equal to the companys current dividend a preferred stock 
that will reflect any increase in the dividend and an equity 
appreciation certificate that will reflect stock price appreciation 
in excess of the bonds stated value 
it is expected that each of the units will trade separately on 
the new york stock exchange along with the companys common stock 
and a unit that will combine the preferred stock and equity 
appreciation certificate 
the stock exchange recently made a proposal to the sec that would 
allow the issuance of unbundled stock units with certain 
restrictions 
the restrictions include limiting the total outstanding stock 
that can be converted into unbundled units to no more than 25 
percent in addition the voting rights of the remaining 
stockholders should not be adversely affected by an exchange of 
stock for unbundled units and individual shareholders should be 
allowed to swap their shares without a shareholder vote 
gallatin said his firm has no objection to the exchanges 
recommendations and noted that each of the four offerings proposed 
to date are in compliance 
shearson has been briefing institutional investors who are being 
counted on to be major participants in the market for unbundled 
stock units 
among the reservations that some investors have expressed are 
that the exchange will be taxable and that unbundled units carry no 
voting rights some have also questioned how liquid the market for 
the new securities will be and have found it difficult to place a 
value on the preferred and equity appreciation components of the 
unbundled unit 
gallatin said the taxability issue should not pose a problem for 
taxexempt investors such as pension funds and may be an incentive 
for investors who may have a capital loss rather than a gain voting 
rights would be restored in the event of a takeover 
in addition gallatin said those trying to place a value on the 
various pieces of the unbundled stock unit should consider the 
extras in the package as a whole 
while companies can cut dividends they are less likely to skip 
an interest payment and that is what the dividend becomes after the 
share of stock is traded for the unbundled stock unit the bond has 
a face value after 30 years of about 25 times the current stock 
price with the potential for even more with the equity appreciation 
certificate 
in an analysis of the pfizer offering the investment firm 
goldman sachs amp co said its experts have guardedly assigned a 
value of about 510 percent of the price of the common to these new 
guarantees which might be realized if one were to hold the pieces 
for 30 years 
but they added that if investors do not consider the value of 
these provisions attractive enough to offset the lack of common 
voting rights and the potential liquidity problem the offering may 
be untenable 
some investors want to wait until the new securities are in the 
market 
in a recent report for the investment firm oppenheimer amp co 
inc analysts norman weinger and michael metz said the jury is 
still out on the probable success of the new securities and 
described initial reaction as mixed 
but they added were the reaction of market participants to 
remain favorable the incentive would be strong for other companies 
to adopt the proposal 
</TEXT>
